### Describe the bug

`invocationContext.getMethod().getAnnotation(MyInterceptorBinding.class)` is returning `null` on an intercepted static method (which is annotated with `MyInterceptorBinding`).

Using `invocationContext.findIterceptorBinding(MyInterceptorBinding.class)` on the `ArcInvocationContext` seems to work as expected.

### Expected behavior

`invocationContext.getMethod().getAnnotation(MyInterceptorBinding.class)` returns the annotation.

### Actual behavior

`invocationContext.getMethod().getAnnotation(MyInterceptorBinding.class)` returns `null`.

### How to Reproduce?

```
@Inherited
@InterceptorBinding
@Target({ ElementType.TYPE, ElementType.METHOD })
@Retention(RetentionPolicy.RUNTIME)
public @interface MyInterceptorBinding {}

@Interceptor
@MyInterceptorBinding
public class MyInterceptor {

    @AroundInvoke
    public Object invoke(ArcInvocationContext invocationContext) throws Exception {
        System.out.println("Intercepted");
        System.out.println(invocationContext.getMethod().getAnnotation(MyInterceptorBinding.class)); //Prints null
        System.out.println(invocationContext.findIterceptorBinding(MyInterceptorBinding.class)); // Seems to work fine
        return invocationContext.proceed();
    }

}

public class MyClass {

    @MyInterceptorBinding
    public static void myMethod() {
        System.out.println("my method");
    }

}


@QuarkusTest
class MyClassTest {

    @Test
    void test() {
        MyClass.myMethod();
    }

}
```

